data.title: William Winston Roper Trophy

data.text:
The Princeton Varsity Club will host its PVC Youth Sports Clinic on Saturday, September 28th as a part of Future Tigers Day and the Princeton football home opener. The clinic is open to the public and will feature sports stations for children ages 5 to 12.

Fans can stop by Finney-Campbell Fields (located between the Princeton Football Stadium and Roberts Soccer Stadium) between 1:30-2:30p.m. to spend time with their favorite Tigers and learn new sports from a variety of Princeton varsity teams.

Please Note: The clinic is free and does not require a game ticket, but we ask that families please register children to attend. Tickets will be required for any fans wishing to enter Princeton Stadium for the football game following the clinic at 3:00p.m.

Attendees are also encouraged to register for the FREE Princeton Kids Club for kids 12 and under. Upon registration, club members can redeem four free tickets for this football game in addition to other perks throughout the year!

Join fellow Princetonians on Wednesday, October 2nd from 12:00-1:30 p.m. for the fall edition of the PVC Luncheon series, where you will hear updates from several fall season Tiger head coaches and student-athletes, as well as remarks from Ford Family Director of Athletics, John Mack ’00.

The event will take place at the Friend Center (Convocation Room 113) with lunch to be provided. Featured head coaches will be announced shortly. Please RSVP below (or reach out to 609-258-8955) if you plan to attend the Fall Coaches Luncheon – we look forward to seeing you!
